the weight of ice on it.

231
00:14:17,670 --> 00:14:19,630
Amazing, Yoda!

232
00:14:29,260 --> 00:14:34,190
The great artisan Orton's
latest magic cart is complete!

233
00:14:34,190 --> 00:14:35,650
Take it with you.

234
00:14:35,650 --> 00:14:38,820
No, no! We can't accept
such an expensive gift!

235
00:14:38,820 --> 00:14:40,280
Don't say that.

236
00:14:40,280 --> 00:14:44,150
I'm not giving you this
just because of what you did today.

237
00:14:44,150 --> 00:14:45,990
Then, why?

238
00:14:45,990 --> 00:14:49,240
You protected our town
the other day, remember?

239
00:14:49,240 --> 00:14:54,080
The hero of Secro deserves
some kind of reward, I'd say.

240
00:14:56,500 --> 00:15:00,420
Take good care of
my daddy's magic cart, okay?

241
00:15:01,380 --> 00:15:03,050
You two...

242
00:15:04,050 --> 00:15:07,760
It's a reward to you
for all your hard work.

243
00:15:08,550 --> 00:15:11,180
A reward... I see.

244
00:15:11,640 --> 00:15:13,680
I'll use it with all my gratitude!

245
00:15:14,600 --> 00:15:15,980
TELULU LEVEL 4

246
00:15:18,230 --> 00:15:19,270
All right.

247
00:15:23,360 --> 00:15:25,990
Oops, looks like it's over capacity.

248
00:15:25,990 --> 00:15:30,530
We've gathered over twice as many bamboo
shoots as usual thanks to the magic cart.

249
00:15:30,530 --> 00:15:33,370
Man, this thing is incredibly handy!

250
00:15:33,370 --> 00:15:34,660
Isn't it?

251
00:15:34,660 --> 00:15:36,790
We must be grateful to Orton and Olga.

252
00:15:36,790 --> 00:15:38,000
For sure.

253
00:15:38,000 --> 00:15:42,590
I'm gonna run over to
Erza's place and sell her these.

254
00:15:42,590 --> 00:15:47,010
Then I'll head home
and start making dinner.

255
00:15:49,510 --> 00:15:51,140
Gimme a break!

256
00:15:51,640 --> 00:15:56,560
Sir, as I've told you several times,
there's no mistake in this purchaseâ€”

257
00:15:57,100 --> 00:15:58,440
Shut your mouth!

258
00:15:58,440 --> 00:16:00,190
I brought enough to sell

259
00:16:00,190 --> 00:16:01,150
- for more than 10,000 pilos!

260
00:16:01,150 --> 00:16:02,020
- Can't someone stop him?
- for more than 10,000 pilos!

261
00:16:02,020 --> 00:16:03,190
- Can't someone stop him?
- I bet you're lying about the price anyway!

262
00:16:03,190 --> 00:16:04,940
- Not me. What if he tries
- I bet you're lying about the price anyway!

263
00:16:04,940 --> 00:16:06,490
- to pick a fight with me next?
- C'mon, cough up the cash already!

264
00:16:06,950 --> 00:16:10,030
I'm willing to accept 20,000 for my trouble.

265
00:16:10,030 --> 00:16:16,500
I can't pay more than the list price of
8,400 pilos for what you've brought in.

266
00:16:16,500 --> 00:16:17,870
What?!

267
00:16:17,870 --> 00:16:20,670
You tryin' to go against
a customer's word?!

268
00:16:24,340 --> 00:16:25,920
What the hell?!

269
00:16:26,550 --> 00:16:28,430
You need to stop.

270
00:16:28,430 --> 00:16:29,430
Ryota!

271
00:16:29,430 --> 00:16:30,840
Who the hell are you?!

272
00:16:31,220 --> 00:16:34,600
Erza wouldn't lie about the list price.

273
00:16:34,600 --> 00:16:36,350
I'll prove it to you.

274
00:16:39,940 --> 00:16:44,320
Check that out!
It's Orton's latest magic cart!

275
00:16:44,730 --> 00:16:47,240
How does he have
so many bamboo shoots?

276
00:16:47,240 --> 00:16:49,860
What the hell do you think you're doing?

277
00:16:56,830 --> 00:17:00,170
Erza, how much is one of
these green onions worth?

278
00:17:00,170 --> 00:17:02,630
Huh? It's 120 pilos.

279
00:17:02,630 --> 00:17:03,790
Got it.

280
00:17:04,290 --> 00:17:09,339
This magic cart was made
with rare monsters from Arsenic, right?

281
00:17:09,720 --> 00:17:12,589
So it automatically detects
the weight of its contents

282
00:17:12,589 --> 00:17:15,140
and calculates the total
amount they'll sell for.

283
00:17:17,390 --> 00:17:19,310
8,400 pilos.

284
00:17:19,310 --> 00:17:22,849
It sounds like the exact amount she quoted.

285
00:17:22,849 --> 00:17:26,250
You're in with this shop
to run some scam, aren't you?!

286
00:17:26,250 --> 00:17:30,400
I just happened to walk in here while you
were here. Do you think I could pull that off?

287
00:17:30,400 --> 00:17:33,570
Shut up, you little bamboo shoot bastard!

288
00:17:34,950 --> 00:17:38,500
I'll knock your ass off!

289
00:17:38,500 --> 00:17:40,410
Ryota, watch out!

290
00:17:41,620 --> 00:17:42,620
What?!

291
00:17:42,620 --> 00:17:45,590
Sorry, but I'm gonna need
you to take a little nap.

292
00:17:49,170 --> 00:17:50,720
Whoa!

293
00:17:50,720 --> 00:17:51,510
He just saved her!

294
00:17:55,720 --> 00:17:58,100
You had to bail me out again.

295
00:17:58,100 --> 00:18:00,310
You don't need to worry about that.

296
00:18:00,310 --> 00:18:01,810
But I will.

297
00:18:01,810 --> 00:18:04,520
I'm an item trader.

298
00:18:05,230 --> 00:18:10,990
All the items I sell here were gathered
at risk of life and limb by adventurers.

299
00:18:11,450 --> 00:18:15,030
I'm obligated to handle them
with utmost care.

300
00:18:15,720 --> 00:18:19,490
I want people to feel comfortable
bringing their goods here to sell to me.

301
00:18:20,250 --> 00:18:23,580
But if I have to be helped
out all the time...

302
00:18:24,080 --> 00:18:27,340
It's a bit more than even I can bear.

303
00:18:27,920 --> 00:18:29,960
What's wrong with that?

304
00:18:29,960 --> 00:18:30,710
Huh?

305
00:18:31,130 --> 00:18:33,760
What's wrong with having help?

306
00:18:33,760 --> 00:18:35,340
Everyone needs help.

307
00:18:35,760 --> 00:18:38,470
You've helped me out a bunch, too.

308
00:18:38,920 --> 00:18:41,560
No, really...

309
00:18:42,020 --> 00:18:44,900
I haven't done anything special at all.

310
00:18:44,900 --> 00:18:48,190
You always buy my items
from me with a smile.

311
00:18:48,190 --> 00:18:50,110
You share your cheer with me.

312
00:18:50,860 --> 00:18:52,030
Ryota...

313
00:18:52,820 --> 00:18:57,780
And if anything like this happens again,
I want to protect you.

314
00:18:57,780 --> 00:19:00,790
You scratch my back,
I scratch yours, right?

315
00:19:02,040 --> 00:19:03,410
Right...

316
00:19:03,410 --> 00:19:09,460
Of course, I feel like the help
you give me means a lot more...

317
00:19:19,430 --> 00:19:22,560
Huh?! Um, Erza?!

318
00:19:22,920 --> 00:19:26,140
That wasn't from me as an item trader.

319
00:19:26,140 --> 00:19:28,730
That was a personal kiss from me.

320
00:19:29,190 --> 00:19:31,820
Make sure you remember it, okay?

321
00:19:32,650 --> 00:19:35,150
Well, I need to get back to work.

322
00:19:45,370 --> 00:19:48,460
TELULU LEVEL 4

323
00:19:54,420 --> 00:19:59,340
Before, the most we could make
in one haul was 20,000 pilos.

324
00:19:59,340 --> 00:20:00,470
But now...

325
00:20:05,810 --> 00:20:07,390
200,000?!

326
00:20:07,690 --> 00:20:10,560
We could buy more than 6,000
bean sprouts with that!

327
00:20:10,560 --> 00:20:12,570
With this much saved up...

328
00:20:12,570 --> 00:20:15,360
We have enough for a new house!

329
00:20:24,330 --> 00:20:27,000
I guess it's time to say
goodbye to this house.

330
00:20:27,500 --> 00:20:29,920
It's a bit sad, isn't it?

331
00:20:30,330 --> 00:20:31,630
Yeah.

332
00:20:32,540 --> 00:20:35,300
I have lots of memories here.

333
00:20:35,780 --> 00:20:42,510
Yes, and I learned just how nice it
is to have a place to come home to.

334
00:20:42,510 --> 00:20:44,600
Yeah. Me, too.

335
00:20:46,640 --> 00:20:48,100
20,000 pilos...

336
00:20:48,100 --> 00:20:50,440
After killing slimes for three days,

337
00:20:50,820 --> 00:20:54,360
we finally scraped together
20,000 pilos for rent.

338
00:20:54,360 --> 00:20:58,070
It's no small amount, but...

339
00:20:58,810 --> 00:20:59,820
Yoda?

340
00:21:01,700 --> 00:21:02,620
Emily...

341
00:21:03,700 --> 00:21:06,410
Let's keep our lease on this place.

342
00:21:06,410 --> 00:21:08,870
That way we can come back home anytime,

343
00:21:08,870 --> 00:21:11,420
even after we move to our new house.

344
00:21:11,880 --> 00:21:15,800
Can we?
Wouldn't that be expensive, though?

345
00:21:15,800 --> 00:21:19,300
I think the whole reason we've been
dungeon-diving to make money

346
00:21:19,300 --> 00:21:21,720
was for a time just like this.

347
00:21:22,140 --> 00:21:25,390
I want to use it to protect
the place that's precious to us.

348
00:21:25,890 --> 00:21:27,270
Yoda...

349
00:21:39,900 --> 00:21:41,950
Morning, Emily.

350
00:21:42,440 --> 00:21:44,950
Good morning, Yoda!

351
00:21:44,950 --> 00:21:46,620
Breakfast is ready.

352
00:21:47,620 --> 00:21:50,290
You still make the best
breakfasts ever, Emily!

353
00:21:50,680 --> 00:21:53,630
I think her carrot dishes
are the best, too.

354
00:21:54,090 --> 00:21:56,290
When did you come in?!

355
00:21:56,290 --> 00:21:59,130
Where there are carrots,
there are also rabbits.

356
00:22:00,300 --> 00:22:02,970
I made lots, so it's no problem at all.

357
00:22:03,590 --> 00:22:06,260
Sheesh... I guess that's that.

358
00:22:06,770 --> 00:22:08,430
Let's eat!

